  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale dataset)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A model revision was issued on 2025-11-10 to refine the impeller-tip clearance geometry and update the turbulence closure coefficients. The primary experimental hemolysis dataset was collected and frozen on 2025-10-17 — approximately three weeks prior to that revision. The assessment narrative argues the geometric and turbulence-model changes were 'not material' to the measured hemolysis values because the dataset captures global pump-outlet hemolysis index rather than local clearance-gap quantities; however, no formal re-validation against the revised model build has been performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven show achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels and six remain at marginal parity. Decision recorded as Accepted pending regulatory review.",
